The paper deals with the problem of query inseparability for ALC ontologies, which is a fundamental problem in ontology engineering. ALC is a description logic commonly used in knowledge representation and reasoning, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses model-theoretic criteria and undecidability results, which are common topics in database theory (cs.DB) and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper addresses ontology versioning, modularisation, update, and forgetting, which are important tasks in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of TBox inseparability, which is a topic in description logic (cs.DL).
